hands_on_practices.introduction:
When working with waves, it is natural to assume that the relation $\lambda 
u = c$ applies directly to the peaks of the blackbody spectrum, leading to the misconception that $\lambda_{peak} 
u_{peak} = c$. This exercise reveals a subtle but crucial mathematical detail of Planck's law: the peak's location depends on whether the spectrum is expressed in terms of wavelength or frequency. By calculating the actual value of the ratio $ rac{\lambda_{peak} 
u_{peak}}{c}$, you will gain a more rigorous understanding of how to work with distribution functions in physics and avoid a common conceptual pitfall. [@problem_id:1887147]
